### Banking AI MCP — REST API Examples
### Use with IntelliJ HTTP Client or VS Code REST Client extension
### Set BANKING_API_KEY env var or use the default below

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@apiKey = banking-demo-key-2024
@contentType = application/json

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CUSTOMER ONBOARDING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Onboard a new customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/customers
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "firstName": "Emma",
  "lastName": "Wilson",
  "dateOfBirth": "1992-08-14",
  "gender": "FEMALE",
  "email": "emma.wilson@example.com",
  "mobile": "+447700900999",
  "nationality": "British",
  "panNumber": "EMWIL9999J",
  "idType": "PAN_CARD",
  "idExpiryDate": "2031-12-31",
  "address": {
    "line1": "55 Rose Garden",
    "line2": "Flat 3B",
    "city": "Edinburgh",
    "state": "Scotland",
    "postalCode": "EH1 1BB",
    "country": "GBR"
  },
  "employmentType": "SALARIED",
  "employerName": "FinTech Ltd",
  "annualIncome": 72000,
  "incomeCurrency": "GBP"
}

### 2. Get customer by ID (use ID from response above)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/customers/CUST-00000001
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 3. Get pending KYC customers (compliance queue)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/kyc/pending?page=0&size=10
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 4. Approve KYC
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/customers/CUST-00000004/kyc
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "kycStatus": "VERIFIED"
}

### 5. Reject KYC
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/customers/CUST-00000004/kyc
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "kycStatus": "REJECTED",
  "rejectionReason": "Identity document unclear — resubmit passport"
}

### 6. Complete onboarding
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/onboarding/customers/CUST-00000001/complete
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ACCOUNTS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 7. Open a savings account
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": "CUST-00000001",
  "accountType": "SAVINGS",
  "currency": "GBP",
  "displayName": "Holiday Fund",
  "initialDeposit": 1000.00
}

### 8. Get account details
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/ACC-202401-001001-5
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 9. Get account balance
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/ACC-202401-001001-5/balance
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 10. Get all accounts for a customer
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts?customerId=CUST-00000001
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 11. Block account
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/ACC-202401-001001-5/block?reason=Suspected+fraud+activity
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 12. Unblock account
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/ACC-202401-001001-5/unblock
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PAYMENTS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 13. Initiate a small safe IMPS payment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payments
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": "CUST-00000001",
  "sourceAccountId": "ACC-202401-001001-5",
  "destinationAccountId": "ACC-202401-002001-3",
  "amount": 500.00,
  "currency": "GBP",
  "paymentType": "IMPS",
  "description": "Rent payment"
}

### 14. Initiate a high-value SWIFT (will trigger fraud)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payments
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "customerId": "CUST-00000003",
  "sourceAccountId": "ACC-202401-004001-2",
  "destinationAccountId": "ACC-202401-003001-7",
  "amount": 150000.00,
  "currency": "USD",
  "paymentType": "SWIFT",
  "description": "International wire transfer"
}

### 15. Get payment status (replace with actual paymentId)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payments/PAYMENT-ID-HERE
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 16. Get payment history for an account
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payments?accountId=ACC-202401-001001-5&page=0&size=10
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 17. Get daily spending summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payments/accounts/ACC-202401-001001-5/daily-summary
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 18. Reverse a payment
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payments/PAYMENT-ID-HERE/reverse?reason=Customer+dispute
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI CHAT (MCP-powered)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 19. Simple balance query via AI
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/banking-ai/chat
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "sessionId": "demo-session-1",
  "message": "What is the current balance of account ACC-202401-001001-5?"
}

### 20. Full payment workflow via AI (initiate + fraud check + process)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/banking-ai/chat
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "sessionId": "demo-session-1",
  "message": "Send 500 GBP from ACC-202401-001001-5 to ACC-202401-002001-3 via IMPS for rent. Run fraud check and process if safe."
}

### 21. High-value fraud scenario
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/banking-ai/chat
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "sessionId": "demo-session-2",
  "message": "Initiate a SWIFT transfer of 200000 USD from ACC-202401-004001-2 to ACC-202401-003001-7. Analyse for fraud and take appropriate action with full reasoning."
}

### 22. KYC workflow via AI
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/banking-ai/chat
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "sessionId": "demo-session-3",
  "message": "Show me all customers with pending KYC review. Then approve KYC for CUST-00000004."
}

### 23. Full onboarding via AI
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/banking-ai/chat
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "sessionId": "demo-session-4",
  "message": "Get the profile of customer CUST-00000001. Then tell me all her accounts and their balances."
}

### 24. Clear AI session
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/banking-ai/sessions/demo-session-1
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 25. View session history
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/banking-ai/sessions/demo-session-1/history
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 26. Health check (no auth required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/health

### 27. Metrics
GET {{baseUrl}}/actuator/metrics
X-API-Key: {{apiKey}}

### 28. H2 Console
# Open in browser: http://localhost:8080/h2-console
# JDBC URL: jdbc:h2:mem:bankingdb
# Username: sa  |  Password: (empty)
